Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Halve the @avocado{1} and remove the pit. Scoop out the flesh into a #bowl{}. Crumble in three-quarters of the @Greek style cheese{100%g}. Mash with a #fork{}. Season with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste}.

Halve the @lime{1}.

Season the smashed avocado to taste with salt, pepper and a squeeze of lime juice. Mix well and set aside.

> TIP: Alternatively, toast the bread in the toaster instead.

Halve the @ciabatta{2} lengthways.

Toast in your #toaster{} until golden. Alternatively, warm in the #oven{} for ~{4-6%minutes}.

> TIP: For an optional fried egg, place a pan over medium-high heat with a drizzle of oil. Once hot, crack in your egg (1 per person). Cook until the egg white is cooked and the yolk is your desired firmness, ~{4-5%minutes}. Lower the heat as needed.

Divide the toasted ciabatta between #plates{}.

Spread the @Ballymaloe tomato relish{1%pot} evenly over the cut side of each piece. Top with the avocado.

If you've made one, add your optional @?egg{1}.

Crumble remaining cheese over the top. Finish with a sprinkling of @dried chilli flakes{1%sachet} (use less if you'd like things milder).

Enjoy your ciabatta open faced or sandwiched closed.